o\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Vincent Labrune, president of the Ligue de Football Professionnel, said that football shows the beauty of strength and passion and that Chinese art is a treasure of human civilization and has a profound influence on French art.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1571, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 0.9999999999588454, \"rank\": 4.112235914518632e-11, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}, {\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ligue_de_Football_Professionnel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.611337883393437e-18, \"text\": \"Ligue de Football Professionnel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ligue_de_Football_Professionnel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ligue_de_Football_Professionnel\"}, {\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_art\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chinese art\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_art\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_art\"}, {\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9848226127450252, \"rank\": 0.015056974909351937, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He expressed hope that more French people will appreciate the charm of Chinese art through this exhibition.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", 